ISLAMABAD, Jan. 7 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and 17 others including women and kids injured in a road accident in Pakistan's southwestern Balochistan province Thursday night, local police said. The incident happened in Khuzdar district of the province when a van hit a trailer coming from the opposite direction on a highway in the province, police told media. The van was carrying over 25 people who were on their way to attend the wedding of a relative in the district, according to the reports. The injured and the bodies have been shifted to a nearby hospital where at least three of the wounded are said to be in critical condition.  â– 